id="Sbt4Knqil-34tX-1lx61-2" value="<div style="line-height: 160%;"><div style="text-align: center;"><font style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">Filling The Table:</font></div><div><font style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">1. We gradually increase the weight capacity of the bag from 0 to the given capacity.</font></div><font style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;"><font>2.&nbsp;</font><span style="background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));">We sort the items by weight.</span></font><div><div><font style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">3. The 0th column represents the weight capacity of the bag as 0. So, we cannot pick up any item.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></div></div><div><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">4. The 0th row says there is no item. So, we cannot pick up any item.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">5. We cannot pick up the items in fractions.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">6. Either we pick up the complete item, or we don't pick up the item.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">7. We need to maximize profit based on the bag's weight capacity.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">8. We have two options and we select the maximum value (profit) out of these two options:&nbsp;</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">8.1. maxOf<font style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">(</font></span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px;"><br></span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; value of top-previous cell<font style="color: rgb(255, 0, 255);">,</font>&nbsp;</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px;"><br></span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; profit of the currently selected item + Table <font style="color: rgb(255, 0, 255);">(</font>Current row - 1, Weight of the currently selected column - Weight of the currently selected item<font style="color: rgb(255, 0, 255);">)</font><font style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">)</font></span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;"><font style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">8.2. For example: (Consider: 0th-based index-rows-columns-table): The value of the last cell:</font></span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;"><font style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">T[i4, w5] = maxOf ( 6, 1 + T[ 4 - 1, 5 - 5 ] ) = maxOf ( 6, 1 + T [ 3, 0 ] ) = maxOf ( 6, 1 + 0 ) = maxOf ( 6, 1 ) = 6</font></span></div><div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;"><font style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></font></span></div><div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0px;"><br></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 160%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div></div>" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;resizeWidth=1;resizeHeight=1;treeMoving=1;spacingTop=0;spacingBottom=0;strokeWidth=1;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="1080" y="80" width="1010" height="480" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Sbt4Knqil-34tX-1lx61-6" value="<div style="line-height: 160%;"><div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px;">Backtracking:&nbsp;</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px;">1. We start from the last cell. Select the last cell.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px;">2. Check if we have the same value in the previous rows (moving upward = moving backward).&nbsp;</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px;">2.1 For example, suppose we have a total of 6 rows.&nbsp;</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;">2.2 So, we start from the last row. That is to say, the 6th row.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;">2.3 Now, suppose the last cell of the last row, that is to say, the last cell of the table has value `6`.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;">2.4 So, we move upward (= backward) to the 5th row and check if it also has the value `6`.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;">2.5 We keep moving upward ( = backward) until we get the last row that has the same value `6`.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;">2.6 For example, suppose the 5th row has also the value `6`, but the 4th row does not have the value `6`.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;">2.7 So, we stop at the 5th row and consider that item as included and discard the items associated with the below rows.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px;">3. Once we find which item we have selected, we can continue the next steps either with the profit or with the weight of the selected item.</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px;">4. For example, suppose the weight of the selected item is `4` and the weight column of the value `6` is 5, then we can do:&nbsp;</span></div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px;">4.1 Weight column value - weight of the item = next number to track (next row = i - 1 and column = `5` - `4` = `1`=&gt; 1st column in our example) or<br>4.2 Profit of the last selected cell (`6` in our example) - Profit of the selected item = next number to track (next row = i - 1 and column = `6` - `4` = `2` =&gt; `2` as the first value in a row in our example).<br>4.3 Repeat the process until we reach 0 as the remaining weight, remaining profit, or the row/column.</span></div></div>" style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;resizeWidth=1;resizeHeight=1;treeMoving=1;fontSize=12;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="240" y="644" width="1980" height="516" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="Xr-yvV-XyORTKlzFm6Zx-1" value="" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;rounded=0;" edge="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry width="50" height="50" relative="1" as="geometry"> <mxPoint x="980" y="490" as="sourcePoint" /> <mxPoint x="980" y="440" as="targetPoint" /> </mxGeometry> </mxCell> <mxCell id="3rXJU2aCyEhyXhpTbRxw-1" value="" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;rounded=0;" edge="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry width="50" height="50" relative="1" as="geometry"> <mxPoint x="620" y="330" as="sourcePoint" /> <mxPoint x="620" y="280" as="targetPoint" /> </mxGeometry> </mxCell> <mxCell id="3rXJU2aCyEhyXhpTbRxw-2" value="" style="endArrow=none;html=1;rounded=0;entryX=1;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;" edge="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry width="50" height="50" relative="1" as="geometry"> <mxPoint x="240" y="631" as="sourcePoint" /> <mxPoint x="2220" y="631" as="targetPoint" /> </mxGeometry> </mxCell> <mxCell id="3rXJU2aCyEhyXhpTbRxw-3" value="<font style="font-size: 25px;"><b>0 / 1 Knapsack</b></font>" style="text;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;resizeWidth=1;resizeHeight=1;treeMoving=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="1140" y="40" width="282" height="30" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> </root> </mxGraphModel> </diagram> </mxfile>

div.span: Backtracking:

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;
div.span: 1. We start from the last cell. Select the last cell.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;
div.span: 2. Check if we have the same value in the previous rows (moving upward = moving backward).

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;
div.span: 2.1 For example, suppose we have a total of 6 rows.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;

span.style: color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;

div.span: 2.2 So, we start from the last row. That is to say, the 6th row.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;

span.style: color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;

div.span: 2.3 Now, suppose the last cell of the last row, that is to say, the last cell of the table has value `6`.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;

span.style: color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;

div.span: 2.4 So, we move upward (= backward) to the 5th row and check if it also has the value `6`.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;

span.style: color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;

div.span: 2.5 We keep moving upward ( = backward) until we get the last row that has the same value `6`.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;

span.style: color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(237, 237, 237)); font-size: 20px; background-color: transparent; line-height: 32px;

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;

div.span: 2.7 So, we stop at the 5th row and consider that item as included and discard the items associated with the below rows.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;
div.span: 3. Once we find which item we have selected, we can continue the next steps either with the profit or with the weight of the selected item.

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;
div.span: 4. For example, suppose the weight of the selected item is `4` and the weight column of the value `6` is 5, then we can do:

div.style: margin-bottom: 0px;
div.span:
4.1 Weight column value - weight of the item = next number to track (next row = i - 1 and column = `5` - `4` = `1`=> 1st column in our example) or
4.2 Profit of the last selected cell (`6` in our example) - Profit of the selected item = next number to track (next row = i - 1 and column = `6` - `4` = `2` => `2` as the first value in a row in our example).
4.3 Repeat the process until we reach 0 as the remaining weight, remaining profit, or the row/column.
